  "prompt": "Got a call frm Amazon's HR that I've been selected. Now the process is struck in Finance Dept. Are there chances that they'll withdraw the offer?",
  "response": "While being stuck in the finance department's review is common, it doesn't necessarily mean the offer will be withdrawn. Here are some points to consider:\n\n1. Normal Process:\n- Finance review is a standard part of hiring\n- Many candidates experience temporary delays\n- Not an automatic red flag\n\n2. Potential Reasons for Delay:\n- Budget verification\n- Background check processing\n- Salary/compensation alignment\n- Internal approvals\n\n3. What You Can Do:\n- Stay patient\n- Maintain professional communication\n- Follow up politely with HR after 3-5 business days\n- Ask about expected timeline\n- Keep documentation of offer\n\n4. Unlikely Scenarios:\n- Offer withdrawal is rare at this stage\n- Most delays are procedural\n- If qualified and offer was made, company typically wants to complete hiring\n\n5. Red Flags to Watch:\n- Repeated vague responses\n- Lack of communication\n- Sudden change in offer terms\n\nRecommendation:\n- Stay positive\n- Keep communication open\n- Don't panic\n- Continue preparation for joining\n\nMost likely, this is just a standard processing step in Amazon's hiring workflow.",
